      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, flickering lights and erratic dashboard illumination are classic symptoms of an alternator that isn't maintaining a steady voltage output, which causes power fluctuations when going into and out of gear. However, modern cars also have fuses and voltage regulators built into the system that can fail and cause similar electrical spikes without immediately letting you know. While wiring issues and loose battery connections are definitely possible causes, starting with a test of your alternator's output at an auto parts store is often the most efficient first step before celebrating too early if you find other components at fault.",
