    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you should also watch for the lights turning unexpectedly dim while driving, difficulty starting the car if it happened at night or in colder weather, or a completely dead battery after a short drive since the alternator failed to charge it. Additionally, if you notice a faint smell of burning rubber from under the hood, that could indicate the drive belt has worn out or the pulley is slipping on the alternator. While unusual dashboard glitches are certainly annoying, these longer-term signs can help confirm whether the issue is truly electrical or something more like a failing alternator that needs replacement soon.",
